This task differed from the choice-RT task in one aspect: the words “right” or “left” could be displayed on either the right or the left side of the cross. The participants were required to press the “j” key if they saw the word “right” (even if it appeared on the left side of the cross) and to press the “f” key if they saw the word “left” (even if it appeared on the right side of the cross; see 
 Figure 1B; 
 Simon and Wolf, 1963; 
 Lu and Proctor, 1995).
